 7:  *   3. Runs `next build`
 8:  *   4. Restores both files (even if build fails)
 9:  *
10:  * Expected result:
11:  *   Build FAILS with:
12:  *     Error: useStrictContext must be used within a StrictContextProvider
13:  *     at react-dom-server.edge.production.js:4282
14:  *
15:  * Why this matters:
16:  *   Next.js 15 uses react-dom-server.edge.production.js (the streaming Edge
17:  *   renderer) even for static page prerendering during `next build`. It does
18:  *   NOT require edge runtime config. Any static page that uses a null-initialised
19:  *   context consumer (createContext(null) + throw) will fail at build time.
20:  *
21:  * The fixed page (/fixed) passes because:
22:  *   - It has getServerSideProps (opts it out of static prerendering)
23:  *   - It uses the withStrictContext HOC (its own provider, seeded before rendering)
24:  */
