  1: /**
  2:  * Standalone reproduction of the Next.js 15 Pages Router + Edge runtime bug.
  3:  *
  4:  * Run: node scripts/simulate-render-order-bug.mjs
  5:  *
  6:  * This script proves that "page renders before _app" is fatal when the context
  7:  * hard-throws on null — exactly what happens with useFlagsmith() on Vercel Edge.
  8:  *
  9:  * The streaming edge renderer (renderToReadableStream) used in Next.js 15 Pages
 10:  * Router on Vercel does NOT guarantee parent-before-child render order, so the
 11:  * page component's function body can execute before _app's Provider mounts.
 12:  *
 13:  * We simulate that race condition below by rendering the page component
 14:  * directly, without any provider ancestor — this is the exact call graph
 15:  * that the broken renderer produces.
 16:  */
